  "insights": {
    "ko": {
      "archetype": "late-bloomer",
      "headline": "Hirohisa Hirukawa: 19년에 걸쳐 59편, 총 8,283회 인용, h=40, 500+ 블록버스터 3편.",
      "paragraphs": [
        "1991년 \"A general algorithm for derivation and analysis of constraint for motion of polyhedra in contact\"으로 출발. 첫 500+ 인용 논문까지 10년 걸림: \"The 3D linear inverted pendulum mode: a simple modeling for a biped walking pattern generation\" (2001, 1,034회). 1000+ 인용 논문: \"The 3D linear inverted pendulum mode: a simple modeling for a biped walking pattern generation\" (2001, 1,034회).",
        "초기 토픽: Polyhedron, Algorithm, Regular polygon. 최근 토픽: Humanoid robot, Computer science, Robot. 피벗 점수 0.41 → 점진적 이동형.",
        "저자수 평균: 초기 3.9명 → 후기 6.5명 (팀 확장).",
        "최다 인용 논문 \"Biped walking pattern generation by using preview control of zero-moment point\" (2003, 2,075회) — 커리어 후기에 위치.",
        "제자 후보 추정 3명 — 상위: Kiyoshi Fujiwara(2001~, 본인 마지막저자 17편), Mitsuharu Morisawa(2005~, 본인 마지막저자 10편), Shinichiro Nakaoka(2002~, 본인 마지막저자 4편)."
      ],
      "lessons": [
        "토픽 적극 피벗 — 정체기를 재창조로 극복한 케이스.",
        "후기에 팀/랩 규모 확장 — 단독 연구자에서 리더로 전환."
      ]
    },
    "en": {
      "archetype": "late-bloomer",
      "headline": "Hirohisa Hirukawa: over 19 years, 59 papers, 8,283 total cites, h=40, 3 blockbusters (500+ cites).",
      "paragraphs": [
        "Started in 1991 with \"A general algorithm for derivation and analysis of constraint for motion of polyhedra in contact\". First 500+ cite paper came 10 years in: \"The 3D linear inverted pendulum mode: a simple modeling for a biped walking pattern generation\" (2001, 1,034 cites). 1000+ cite paper: \"The 3D linear inverted pendulum mode: a simple modeling for a biped walking pattern generation\" (2001, 1,034 cites).",
        "Early topics: Polyhedron, Algorithm, Regular polygon. Recent topics: Humanoid robot, Computer science, Robot. Pivot score 0.41 → gradual shift.",
        "Authors per paper: early 3.9 → late 6.5 (team growth).",
        "Peak paper \"Biped walking pattern generation by using preview control of zero-moment point\" (2003, 2,075 cites) — fell in late career.",
        "3 likely students — top: Kiyoshi Fujiwara(2001~, we last-author on 17), Mitsuharu Morisawa(2005~, we last-author on 10), Shinichiro Nakaoka(2002~, we last-author on 4)."
      ],
      "lessons": [
        "Active topic pivoter — overcame plateau by reinvention.",
        "Late-career team scaling — solo researcher → lab leader."
      ]
    }
  }
